@database "Cyclone V1.25c On Line Help"
@NODE Main "main node"

Help is not available for this topic. Sorry!

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_main "Main Display"
This is Cyclone's main display. At the top of the screen is the header
box which displays information about the currently showing message. At
the bottom of the screen are the control icons:

@{b}Write new message@{ub}

Loads your configured text editor and lets you enter a new message. When
loaded the text editor will display a skeleton message consisting of the
write-header and signature strings you have defined for the current area.
Cyclone is frozen while you enter the message.

Before the text editor loads you will be presented with a message header
window. Here you can enter the name and network address of the intended
recipient, as well as the message subject line.

When you have finished editing the mssage, save and quit the text editor. Your
message will be saved to the current are with an E or Export flag.

* HotKey 'w'


@{b}Reply to current message@{ub}

Similar to the Write function, except that you will be presented with the full
text of the current message included between your intro and sig strings. Each
line of the message will be prefixed with the initials of the sender and a
quote (>) mark.

* HotKey 'r'


@{b}Delete message@{ub}

Removes the current message. There is no way back once you have deleted a
message -- It's gone for good.

* HotKey 'd'


@{b}Back in thread@{ub}

Jumps back to the last message with the same subject line as the one you are
currently on.

* HotKey Shift+Left Cursor

@{b}Move back@{ub}

Moves to the previous message.

* HotKey Left Cursor


@{b}Move forward@{ub}

Moves to the next message.

* HotKey Right Cursor


@{b}Forward in thread@{ub}

Jumps to the next message with the same subject line as the one you are on.

* HotKey Shift+Right Cursor


@{b}Edit message@{ub}

Loads the text editor so you can change the contents of the current message.
Pops up the header window so you can change the details there too.

* HotKey 'e'


@{b}Message list@{ub}

Displays a list of to/from/subj/date data for all messages in the current
area. Clicking on a message displays it in full. The first four buttons below
the list enable you to set/unset the Export and Marked flags.

* HotKey 'm'


@{b}Area List@{ub}

Displays a list of all available message areas. Clicking on an area saves all
data for the current area and loads in the new one.

* HotKey 'a'


@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_userlist "User List"

User List
=========

To enter a new name in the User List just click the 'Add' button and
fill in the three required fields. Clicking 'Del' will delete the
selected entry.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_nukelist "Nuke List"

Nuke List
=========

To enter a new keyword in the Nuke List just click 'Add' and enter the
required keyword into the string gadget at the bottom of the window.
The four check boxes above it control what fields should be scanned
for the keyword.

Any inbound message will that keyword present in the selected fields
will be deleted at import time.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_search "Area Search"

Area Search
===========

From this window you can search the current area for a specified
word(s). The check boxes in the middle of the window control what
fields should be searched for the keywords. If you select the 'Marked'
box then the keywords you have entered are ignored and Cyclone will
search for any messages with a (M) Marked flag.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_savetext "ASCII Save"

ASCII Save
==========

Dumps the current message into a standard text file. All kludges will
be stripped, but Seen-By lines are not.

Clicking the Header gadget will prefix the text with header information.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_userprefs "Tosser Prefs"

Tosser Preferences
==================

 Name          : The name you are known by.

 User Alias    : Your alias. Used in any areas with the 'Alias' flag set.
                 Please note that aliases are prohibited on some networks.

 Dupe Checking : Toggles duplicate message checking. If you rarely get dupes
                 it's best to leave this disabled as dupe checking can slow
                 import operations considerably, especially using larger
                 table sizes.

 Table Size    : Size of the table used to store message IDs. The entire
                 table must be scanned for every message imported, so keep
                 it as small as possible.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_genprefs "General Prefs"

General Preferences
===================

This window shows all the paths and command strings used by Cyclone. Some of
them, such as the editor & poll commands, must be altered to fit your system.

 Editor     : Path and filename of the text editor used for entering and
              editing messages.
 Edit File  : Temporary file used to store the message being edited.
 Inbound    : Path of the directory where incoming packets are stored
 Outbound   : Path of the directory where outgoing packets are sotred
 Compress   : Master Compress command. Name and path of the archiver used
              to compress outgoing mail. This command is used only as the
              default for new networks.
 Expand     : Name and path of the archiver used to uncompress inbound mail
 Poll       : Master Poll command. Name and path of the mailer used to send
              and receive mail. This command is used only as the default for
              new networks.
 Pkt Backup : Path of the directory used to backup incoming mail packets
              before an import operation. Entering a null path disables
              packet backup.
 Ascii Save : Default path for saved messages.
 F-Attach   : Default path for file attaches
 Arexx      : Default path for Arexx Scripts. Best left as Cyclone:Arexx
 File Backup: Path of the directory used to backup any files in the INBOUND
              directory before an import operation. Entering a null path
              disables file backup.
 Polling    : Controls the method used to call the mailer program.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_networks "Network Prefs"

Network Preferences
===================

Any additional FTNs you wish to access are configured from this
window. Please note that new areas will use the first listed network.
If areas are to use data for other nets they must be attached to that
network manually via the Preferences/Areas window.

Netmail areas for new networks will be automaticaly created when you close
the Networks window.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_areaprefs "Area Prefs"

Attributes for all available areas can be changed from this window. Areas are
listed on the left hand side, with flags at the top right and strings below
them.

The Flags are:

 Netmail  : Sets this area to a Netmail area.
 Frozen   : Prevents Purge operations.
 Read Only: Prevents message delete.
 R. Tags  : Appends a random tagline to any message you write.
 E-Mail   : Flags a netmail area as connected to an e-mail gateway.
 Alias    : Use alias instead of real user name.


@{b}Name@{ub}

If you dislike the tag name of an area you can enter a replacement name
here. This will be used by the area list window only. The following control
codes can be used as the first character of the name to change the way this
area appears in the main area list window:

 !  : Highlight
 *  : Bold
 -  : Seperator Line (above name)
 _  : Seperator Line (below name)


@endnode

@NODE wi_rexprefs "ARexx Prefs"

ARexx Preferences
=================

Any ARexx scripts you wish to make available for instant use via the ARexx 
menu are entered here.

Name : The name that will appear on the ARexx menu

Script : Name and path of the script to execute

Output : Destination of any textual output from the script. This defaults
to NIL and should be left as such if possible. Cyclone's requester boxes
should be used for output instead.

The ARexx interpreter (RexxMast) must be running before any ARexx scripts
can be called.


@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_wintro "Write Intros"

Write Intros
============

This window is used to create headers for any messages you create
using the 'Write' function. To create a new header just click the
'Add' button. Several control codes are available in Write Headers:

 |n   Newline
 |t   Name of intended recipient
 |T   As above but first name only
 |d   Current date
 |u   Your name

The normal * (bold), _ (Underline) and / (Italic) codes can be used
here as well. A preview of how your header will look appears at the
bottom of the window.

If you find the built-in editor limiting all Write Intro headers are
stored as plain ASCII in the file 'Cyclone:Wintros.Dat'. Be careful
not to let your headers exceed 350 characters if editing this file
with a text editor.

If you wish an area to use a new header you must configure the area
via the Preferences/Areas window.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_gui "GUI"

Here you can control what, if any, entries on the message and area lists
should be picked out in bold.

@endnode

@NODE wi_shunt "Mail Shunt"

Mail shunting is one of Cyclone's most powerful features. It takes inbound
messages and re-directs them to a new area based on keywords present in the
subject line. Each 'Shunt Link' requires three parameters:

 From Area   : Area to be scanned for matching messages
 To Area     : Shunted messages end up here
 Subject     : Messages with this subject are shunted

You can place a 4D fido address in the Subject field here and any messaged
originating from that address will be shunted.

@endnode

@NODE wi_rintro "Reply Intros"

Reply Intros
============

As Write intros except headers created here will be used when you reply
to a message. Two additional codes are available : |f (name of sender) and
|F (as |f but first name only) ASCII data for reply headers is stored in
'Cyclone:Rintros.Dat'. The 350 char limit applies here also.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_sig "Sigs"

Signatures
==========

Signatures are small texts appended to the bottom of any non-netmail
messages you write. ASCII data for the signatures is held in the file
'Cyclone:Sigs.Dat'. Sigs can be quite elaborate, but it's best not to
use the /*_ control chars because all fido message editing software
will interpret these in slightly different ways. What looks good using
Cyclone may look silly using other software.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_origin "Origins"

Origins
=======

Origin lines are placed below a signature line and prefixed with ' *
Origin'. They are supposed to carry the name of the node at which the
message originated, but many people use them as mini taglines. The /*_
control chars are available for origins, but | prefixed codes are not.
ASCII data for origins is stored in 'Cyclone:Origins.Dat' with a 58
char line limit.

@ENDNODE


@NODE wi_freq "Freq Window"

File Request
============

The file request (Freq) window allows you to request files from any
Fidonet node that supports this feature.

To request a file just type the address of the fido node into the
string gadget at the top of the window. Then enter the files you want
in the string gadget in the bottom part of the window.

When you close the window a Freq (.REQ) packet will be created in the
OUTBOUND directory. The next time you poll the requested node the
request packet will be sent and, if you're lucky, the files will be
downloaded.

When you type in a fido address any .REQ files destined for that address will
be loaded into the Freq list for editing. Cyclone can load REQ files created
by any Amiga mail package.


@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_msgdisp "Message Display Prefs"

Format Codes
-----------

   Invalid Leading : Text style codes will be ignored if any of the chars
                     in this string are present in front of the code.

   Whitespace      : Characters entered here are considered to be white
                     space.

   Terminators     : Text style codes will be ignored if any of the chars
                     in this string are present behind the code.


Distances
---------

   Attributes      : The maximum number of chars a text style code may
                     affect.

   Quotes          : The number of chars at the beginning of a line that
                     will be scanned for quote (>) chars.


Colours
-------

  This page contains four colour buttons that are used to specify the
  colours used for different quote levels.


Misc
----

  Sig Seperator    : Replaces any occurence of '-- ' with a solid
                     horizontal line.

  Hide PGP Keys    : Hides PGP keys and replaces them with a 'PGP Key
                     detected' string. [Not currently available - GC]

  Text Styles      : Toggles recognition of text syles.

  Hide UU-enocodes : Hides uu-encodes and replaces them with a 'UUencode
                     detected' string.

  Parse FTX codes  : Toggles recognition of FTX colour codes.

@ENDNODE


@NODE wi_all "All List"

Fast Search List
================

Displays a window containing a list of all messages in the current area that
have a TO: field matching the string you enter here. Defaults to 'ALL'.
Clicking on an entry takes you to that message.

@ENDNODE

@NODE wi_thread

Thread Window
=============

Displays a window containing a list of all messages the have the same subject
line as the one you are currently on. Clicking on an entry takes you to that
message.

@ENDNODE


